values:
It was easily the greatest concert i have ever been to.

STP Fucking Rules

It could not have been put any better than what the drunken man said to me as he clutched the telephone pole to keep his balance on the way out, "man, that was fuckin beautiful"

They played almost everything i hoped they would. The only ones i wish they wouldve played were unglued, you cant drive me away, and days of the week. but there were no complaints what so ever. it was amazing. These are the songs I remembered

plush - epic.
interstate love song - beautiful.
sour girl - so happy they played this, seriously.
crackerman - people went apeshit.
big empty - opened with this.
creep - keep singing.
sex type thing - fucking crazy awsome.
big bang baby - chaos.
lady picture show - weiland can fuckin sing.
silvergun superman - bad fucking ass.
dead and bloated - encore #1.
down - intense, killer solo.
trippin on a hole in a paper heart - encore #2, killer solo.
vasoline - brilliant.
wicked garden - amazing.

There were more yet but i cant remember what they were, i was goin crazy. did i mention it was awsome.


Weiland can sing and preform like no other.
the DeLeo brothers can play with the best.
Kretz holds it together and doesnt miss a beat.
It was pure beauty
Raw emotion
Severe intensity
Complete insanity
& Fucking Beautiful

I cant wait for round two, July 18th, Soaring Eagle. It shall be amazing. Fuck Yeah. 

Rock N' Fuckin Roll,
Zack
as of last night. im officially done with high school. hell yes.

Im thinkin this journal is only going to be used for me to write down things i want to remember and to blow off steam from now on. Nobody ever reads it anyway. Except for the dude who read my post about my stp tickets. I dont know who you are but kudos to you, and sorry, i dont have the presale password.



Tonight my dad and i got all of our stuff for the roof, dock, and parts of the deck to the cabin, i cant wait until i can stay up there.

Im trying to stay positive, for the most part i think im doing well.

It was nice driving around with my dad alot tonight. I like driving with him, there are always good talks.


Tonight it was about people and how everyone should learn to live. 


He also gave me my favorite definition of insanity:

Insanity - Repeating the same action and expecting a different outcome.

And last but not least about how people bottle up anger, make the people around them feel like they are an inch tall, only to finish them off with some small remark and an incredible explosion. All of the anger can be subsided by talking and letting people know when they have crossed the line. The worst thing a person can do is pretend nothing is wrong until the damage is done.
After that, there is no turning back.

The sad truth is, The people you hurt the most, are the people you love the most. 

It was a good night, I really enjoy our talks. I just wish more people would think about the things i mentioned. I think it would help everyone.

Learn to Live, Resist insanity, Be Honest, and try not to hurt the ones you Love.

After the most stressful 20 minute ticket finding frezy i will ever undertake in my life. I am now a proud concert goer of the June 3 show at the Fillmore in Detroit to see Stone Temple Pilots. thats right. Mother fucking STP. Their first tour in 8 years and its gonna be fucking rad. 

I was pissed at first due to several errors in the checkout stage because ticketmasters servers were overloading and tickets were going like 12093812979871235821634.237429374 X the speed of sound.
I went from row G of the lower balcony seats 1-5 center stage.... to only 3 seats in the upper balcony in row U... oh well. Im fucking going. And its gonna be fucking rad.
 
I am pretty lucky because after 20 minutes they were sold out of even two seats next to each other. By now if they are not sold out completely there may be a couple single seats left. the last time i checked for a single seat was at 10:45 and there was 1 in the upper balcony far left in row S. The only way you can get a ticket now is if you pay $45 to get in the fan club, plus $240 for a VIP Ticket.

Im not mad at all right now. Because of the 2500 tickets for the show, I have 3 of them. 

Im so fucking amped right now. I cant wait. Fucking right. 

Peace, Love, and Rock and Fucking Roll,
Zack.

im sorry this entry isnt very descriptive, i dont really have much to say.
its just the usual highschool bullshit.
i guess homecoming is comin up soon, i dont know if im doing anything or not yet...

this year has only started and i cant wait for it to end. or at least a break from it.
i just need to get away for a while where i dont have to think about anything going on here.
im getting sick of my luck, nothing ever works out. no matter how great things are looking theres always something that stands in the way.i know it sounds like im whining and complaining, but im just getting sick of it, i just wish that just once great could happen without the catastrophic failure to it. i apologize for all this that im rambling on about. but yet i guess it doesnt matter because i cant believe anyone accually reads this. i would do anything to go back and fix my past mistakes... anything. i was always wrong about what i thought about giving in, but this shits gone way to far. i was wrong, theres nothing wrong with it at all. you can only give up so much before you have to call it quits. its the ghosts of past failures that wont go away and i would do anything to make them go away.

well thats my life
and thats my latest entry.
probly the last one also, at least for a while.
i dont have anythign to write about and i  dont feel my lifes worth reading about anyway.
it doesnt matter anyway.
once again i apologize for the endless shit coming out in this entry but its just how i feel.
this is all for now
have fun.

Today was a day of great highs and lows. to start with the bad news. lastnight "dimebag" darrell abbot was shot 5 times point blank on stage during a concert and died. the guy shot 3 other people and 2 people are in intensive care. he shot at the other bandmembers too but they didnt say anything about any of them injured. for you who dont know. dime was the legendary guitarist of the former pantera and what was damage plan until last night. 24 years ago a great mind was killed. december 8th 1980. that mans name was john lennon. shot it the back several times by a crazed fan. 24 years later a man decided to end the life of another great musician. there is suspected to be a grudge or a motive to the killing but nothing is known yet. the gunman was shot and killed by police before killing a hostage or anyone else in the club. lastnight changed the metal world without a doubt as the world of metal mourns the loss of dimebag.

in other news i got to pick up my guitar and it it awsome, that dude is great. sounds and plays heavenly. but now i dont get it until christmas so thats gonna be tough. 

im off to bed, gonna catch the one hour tribute to dimebag tonight at midnight on z93. thats it for now.

just a long sad day.

well here i am sittin around at home. i ended up goin to school today after lunch, i still felt like crap though. i dont know exactly what im doin tomarrow. i am goin to guitar society tomarrow tho for sure. thats a givin, no way i will miss that. i might try to go to beccas game but im not sure if im goin or not. other than that its just a ton of homework and stuff for tomarrow... the normal stuff. anyway, back to the HOLY SHITBALLS statement, that is because parent teacher confrences are goin on and i am praying i didnt get anythign below a b- because them im screwed. while im pateintly waiting i am workin on rebuilding my chops because i lost them during football season. well im goin back to my guitar, i will post later or something

Right now i am stuck at home sick and i thought i would make a new journal thing, so here i am. poor kids, right now ms rech it teaching them gymnastics, i should feel bad for them but... i dont. anyways, so far today i have woke up, then when back to sleep. so its been a very exciting day. just been playin some guitar too. Not much has been goin on latley tho.

since football ended i have just been sittin around playing guitar and ridin a little bit again. i start liftin monday so that will at least give me somethin to do. havent been able to take the quad out either, i need new wheels on it so it will be a while before i will be ridin.

tomarow night i get to go to a much needed jam session for the first time in a few months... i cant wait, i need to go and just play for a few hours and clear my head. i cant wait, its gonna be sweet

im out.
